00:03:58.757 --> 00:04:01.252
where F is a function
continuous at every point

00:04:01.252 --> 00:04:02.865
of the interval.

00:04:02.865 --> 00:04:05.822
The closed interval, from A to B.

00:04:05.822 --> 00:04:07.472
Now, given that

00:04:07.472 --> 00:04:09.913
there's two ways to state the conclusion

00:04:09.913 --> 00:04:11.767
for the intermediate value theorem.

00:04:11.767 --> 00:04:13.450
You'll see it written in one of these ways

00:04:13.450 --> 00:04:14.970
or something close to one of these ways.

00:04:14.970 --> 00:04:16.784
And that's why I included both of these.

00:04:16.784 --> 00:04:18.554
So one way to say it is, well

00:04:18.554 --> 00:04:20.521
if this first statement is true

00:04:20.521 --> 00:04:22.953
